						<summary>

						<p>On the beam at the entrance of the Narasiṁhasvāmin temple on the Narasiṁhakoṇḍa hill.</p>						

						<p>Velamapāṭi Tiramalarājayadēva-mahārāja.</p>						

						<p>Dated in <hi rend="italic">Piṅgaḷa, Kārtika,</hi> śu. 15 (in the 16th-17th century characters).</p>						

						<p>Records the gift of a tank to the god by the chief. (cf. <hi rend="italic">Inscriptions of the Nellore District,</hi> Part II, pp. 804-805, No. 35). He is described as a mahāmaṇḍalēśvara and bears the epithets, Chāḷukyanārāyaṇa, Chauhattamalla and raṇavijaya.</p>						

